WN10-SO-000185 - PKU2U authentication using online identities must be prevented.


1. Tenable Discovered STIGS FAILURE WN10-SO-000185
Registry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE
Registry Path: \SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\LSA\pku2u\

Value Name: AllowOnlineID

Value Type: REG_DWORD
Value: 0

2. Followed advice given from Tenanble in the Check cololum

3.Found that \pku2u\ and value AllowOnlineID doesn't exist
4. Created the following pathway through powershell and value to log size: The code is below

# Define registry path and value
$regPath = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\LSA\pku2u\"
$name = "AllowOnlineID"
$value = 0

# Create path if it doesn't exist
if (-not (Test-Path $regPath)) {
Â    New-Item -Path $regPath -Force | Out-Null
}

# Set the value
Set-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name $name -Value $value -Type DWord

5. Restarted the computer and check if value was there. The value was there
6. Run Tenable andWN10-SO-000185 passed
